FuncDef:
The radius-attribute framed-route support default-route command enables the device to generate a default route based on the route carried in the Framed-Route attribute delivered by the RADIUS server.
The undo radius-attribute framed-route support default-route command restores the default configuration.
By default, the device does not generate a default route based on the route carried in the Framed-Route attribute delivered by the RADIUS server.
ExtraInfo:
Usage Scenario
To enable the device to generate a default route based on the route carried in the Framed-Route attribute delivered by the RADIUS server, run the radius-attribute framed-route support default-route command.
Precautions
In VS mode, this command is supported only by the admin VS.
